def: A shrub or small tree of the genus Corylus, as the C. avellana,bearing a nut containing a kernel of a mild, farinaceous taste; thefilbert. The American species are C. Americana, which produces thecommon hazelnut, and C. rostrata. See Filbert. Gray.
A scoop or ring with either a blunt or a cutting edge, forremoving substances from the walls of a cavity, as from the eye, ear,or womb.
The state of being relative; as, the relativity of a subject.Coleridge.
A wading bird of the genus Grus, and allied genera, of variousspecies, having a long, straight bill, and long legs and neck.
Deprived of, or removed from, a bower. [Poetic] Bryant.
A mark of reference; -- called also dagger [&dag;]. See Dagger,n., 2.
